  <section id="chapter_all">
  <bookmark branch="index" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3156324"><bookmark_value>titles; changing</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>headings; changing document titles</bookmark_value><bookmark_value>documents; changing titles</bookmark_value></bookmark><paragraph id="hd_id3156324" role="heading" level="1" oldref="1" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><variable id="change_title"><link href="text/shared/guide/change_title.xhp" name="Changing the Title of a Document">Changing the Title of a Document</link></variable></paragraph>
  <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="paragraph" id="par_id3150247" l10n="U" oldref="2">The title of the current document is displayed on the title bar of <item type="productname">%PRODUCTNAME</item>.</paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3152801" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="3">When you create and save a document for the first time, the title is the same as the file name.</paragraph>
  <paragraph role="heading" level="2" id="hd_id3156136" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="4">How to change the title of the current document</paragraph>
  <list type="ordered">
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="5" role="listitem" id="par_id3153345" l10n="U">Choose <emph>File - Properties</emph>. This opens the <emph>Properties of</emph> dialog.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="listitem" id="par_id3156410" l10n="U" oldref="6">Select the <emph>Description</emph> tab.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" oldref="7" role="listitem" id="par_id3147242" l10n="U">Type the new title in the <emph>Title</emph> box and click <emph>OK</emph>.</paragraph>
   </listitem>
  </list>
  </section>
